<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B029FE6BFE11AC13" authority="Meijere" authorityName="Meijere" box="[845,1100,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B029FE6BF98BAC12" box="[845,982,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. provecta</emphasis>
(Meijere)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B73DFE6BFF62AC13" authority="Zehntner" authorityName="Zehntner" box="[1113,1343,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sojae">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B73DFE6BFEE6AC12" box="[1113,1211,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. sojae</emphasis>
(Zehntner)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B619FE6BFB0DAC3F" authority="Sasakawa" authorityName="Sasakawa" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yodai">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B619FE6BFA88AC3F" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. yodai</emphasis>
Sasakawa
</taxonomicName>
, have previously been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="44AE48CB0644FFF7B06AFDB6F92FAC3F" box="[782,882,546,571]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(Sasakawa 1962, 1963a, 1977, 19181; Spencer 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B3F3FDD2FA8CAC5B" box="[151,209,582,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="1961.0">1961</number>
a, 1973, 1986).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C06085B0644FFF7B3A3FDFFF827ADC2" blockId="3.[151,1437,402,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
In this paper, 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B205FDFFFB20AC87" box="[353,381,619,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="12.0">12</number>
species, excluding five known Oriental species, are recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="44AE48CB0644FFF7B716FDFEFE8BAC87" box="[1138,1238,618,643]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">Thailand</collectingCountry>
for the first time, of which 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B263FD1BFB7EACA3" box="[263,291,655,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="10.0">10</number>
are new to science. Most of the flies described and discussed below belong to a group of shining coppery-greenish, black species that occur throughout the Old World tropics. Only six species, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B7A0FD20FF69ACCF" box="[1220,1332,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancyla" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B7A0FD20FF69ACCF" box="[1220,1332,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. ancyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15FE69320644FFF7B658FD26FFC9ACCE" box="[1340,1428,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B658FD26FF0BACCF" bold="true" box="[1340,1366,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B600FD26FFD3ACCF" bold="true" box="[1380,1422,690,715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B3F3FD43FB97ACEA" authority="Sasakawa, M." authorityName="Sasakawa, M." box="[151,458,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gressitti">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B3F3FD43FB46ACEA" box="[151,283,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. gressitti</emphasis>
Sasakawa, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B2CFFD43FB97ACEA" box="[427,458,727,750]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunulata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B2CFFD43FB97ACEA" box="[427,458,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
lunulata 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15FE69320644FFF7B125FD42F8C2ACEA" box="[577,671,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B125FD42F806ACEB" bold="true" box="[577,603,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B10BFD42F8C4ACEB" bold="true" box="[623,665,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B1D0FD43F938ACEB" box="[692,869,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pandiculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B1D0FD43F938ACEB" box="[692,869,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. pandiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15FE69320644FFF7B016FD42F98CACEA" box="[882,977,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B016FD42F9D1ACEB" bold="true" box="[882,908,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B0C5FD42F996ACEB" bold="true" box="[929,971,726,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B082FD43FEB1ACEB" authority="Meijere" authorityName="Meijere" box="[998,1260,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B082FD43FE2FACEA" box="[998,1138,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. provecta</emphasis>
(Meijere)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B656FD43FB55AD17" authority="Sasakawa" authorityName="Sasakawa" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yodai">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B656FD43FFC1ACEB" box="[1330,1436,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. yodai</emphasis>
Sasakawa
</taxonomicName>
, lack the coppery-greenish sheen on the mesoscutum and abdomen. The color of the fringe on the calypter, which is either white to yellowish-white or brown to black, is an essential differentiating character among the species. The pale fringe is seen in most of the 
<collectingCountry id="44AE48CB0644FFF7B1A9FCD6F96CAD5F" box="[717,817,834,859]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">Thailand</collectingCountry>
species, and only seven species have a dark fringe: 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B619FCD0FABFAD7B" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ancyla" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B619FCD0FABFAD7B" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. ancyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15FE69320644FFF7B38DFCF2FB1FAD7A" box="[233,322,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B38DFCF2FB5EAD7B" bold="true" box="[233,259,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B276FCF2FB61AD7B" bold="true" box="[274,316,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B235FCF3FB86AD7B" box="[337,475,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalexis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B235FCF3FB86AD7B" box="[337,475,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. catalexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15FE69320644FFF7B286FCF2F867AD7A" box="[482,570,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B286FCF2F868AD7B" bold="true" box="[482,565,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B12EFCF3F895AD7A" box="[586,712,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gressitti">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B12EFCF3F895AD7A" box="[586,712,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. gressitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B1B3FCF3F907AD7B" box="[727,858,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunulata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B1B3FCF3F907AD7B" box="[727,858,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. lunulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15FE69320644FFF7B006FCF2F9E7AD7A" box="[866,954,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B006FCF2F921AD7B" bold="true" box="[866,892,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B0EFFCF2F9E8AD7B" bold="true" box="[907,949,870,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B0AEFCF3FF52AD7A" authority="Sasakawa, M." authorityName="Sasakawa, M." box="[970,1295,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayensis">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B0AEFCF3FE31AD7B" box="[970,1132,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. malayensis</emphasis>
Sasakawa, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B794FCF3FF52AD7A" box="[1264,1295,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pandiculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B794FCF3FF52AD7A" box="[1264,1295,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
pandiculata 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15FE69320644FFF7B3F3FC1EFAADADA6" box="[151,240,906,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B3F3FC1EFAECADA7" bold="true" box="[151,177,906,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B3A4FC1EFAB7ADA7" bold="true" box="[192,234,906,931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B255FC18FBE5ADA7" box="[305,440,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="provecta">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B255FC18FBE5ADA7" box="[305,440,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. provecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The males of some species with a pale fringe can be further characterized by eyes that are whitish-pilose on the anterodorsal area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C06085B0644FFF7B3A3FC46F84FAA36" blockId="3.[151,1437,402,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
This is the dominant genus in 
<collectingCountry id="44AE48CB0644FFF7B178FC46F8DDADEF" box="[540,640,978,1003]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">Thailand</collectingCountry>
as well as in other Oriental countries. It is also notable that 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B643FC46FF1EADEF" box="[1319,1347,978,1003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="16.0">16</number>
species of 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B3D3FC62FA8EAA0B" box="[183,211,1014,1039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="25.0">25</number>
known species are treated here as endemic, although some of them will likely be found in other Oriental- Oceanian countries in due course.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C06085B0644FFF7B3A3FBAAFF4DABE7" blockId="3.[151,1437,402,1507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Special attention should be drawn to both thoracic coloration and male genitalic features in the following species. Firstly, three of the new species, 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B10DFBF0F8AEAA7F" box="[617,755,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catalexis">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B10DFBF0F8AEAA7F" box="[617,755,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. catalexis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="A48214DE0644FFF7B066FBF6F90BAA7F" box="[770,854,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1374,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1379,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 18. Male genitalia of Melanagromyza catalexis sp. nov. (9 – 11, holotype), M. cirrappendicula sp. nov. (12 – 14, holotype) and M. lunulata sp. nov. (15 – 18, holotype). 9, 12, 15, surstylus; 10, 13, 16, phallus, lateral view; 11, 14, 17, phallus, ventral view; 18, ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B053FBF7F90BAA7F" box="[823,854,1123,1147]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B00FFBF6F994AA7F" box="[875,969,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lunulata">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B00FFBF6F994AA7F" box="[875,969,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">lunulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="A48214DE0644FFF7B0B3FBF6FE74AA7F" box="[983,1065,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[202,1374,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[197,1379,193,1907]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 18. Male genitalia of Melanagromyza catalexis sp. nov. (9 – 11, holotype), M. cirrappendicula sp. nov. (12 – 14, holotype) and M. lunulata sp. nov. (15 – 18, holotype). 9, 12, 15, surstylus; 10, 13, 16, phallus, lateral view; 11, 14, 17, phallus, ventral view; 18, ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216907/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B768FBF6FE74AA7F" box="[1036,1065,1122,1147]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B70DFBF6FEB2AA7F" box="[1129,1263,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pandiculata">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B70DFBF6FEB2AA7F" box="[1129,1263,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">pandiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="A48214DE0644FFF7B79AFBF6FF0FAA7F" box="[1278,1362,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 36" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,197,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 36. Male genitalia of Melanagromyza pandiculata sp. nov. (30 – 32, holotype) and M. sexseriata sp. nov. (33 – 36, holotype)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216909/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">
Fig. 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B657FBF7FF0FAA7F" box="[1331,1362,1123,1147]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
), have a distinct phallus with a membranous swelling on ventral side. It indicates a close relationship with the following species: Palaearctic, Oriental, Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B1EEFB38F9DFAAC7" authority="Hendel" authorityName="Hendel" box="[650,898,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B1EEFB38F97BAAC7" box="[650,806,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. pubescens</emphasis>
Hendel
</taxonomicName>
(
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B0F1FB3FF98CAAC7" box="[917,977,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="1923.0">1923</number>
; Sasakawa 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B73EFB3EFECBAAC7" box="[1114,1174,1194,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="1996.0">1996</number>
: fig. 
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B7B1FB3FFEB8AAC7" box="[1237,1253,1195,1219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="2.0">2</number>
), Australian 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B619FB38FB1AAAE3" authority="Spencer" authorityName="Spencer" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anceps">
<emphasis id="0ECDD4490644FFF7B619FB38FAB8AAE2" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="504">M. anceps</emphasis>
Spencer
</taxonomicName>
(
<number id="8A711A7C0644FFF7B233FB5AFBCEAAE3" box="[343,403,1230,1255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" value="1977.0">1977</number>
b: figs 5, 6), 
<taxonomicName id="FBB973D80644FFF7B140FB5BF97BAAE3" authority="Spencer" authorityName="Spencer" box="[548,806,1231,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="504" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avicenniae">
